How to Synchronize Two Remote Git Repositories.
如何同步兩個遠端 Git 儲存庫。

No war in Ukraine. Stop Russia!
烏克蘭沒有戰爭。阻止俄羅斯！

oleksii_y

2 min read
·
Nov 22, 2018

Preface  前言

Imagine you have two repository URLs and want to synchronize them so that they contain the same thing.
假設您有兩個存儲庫 URL，並希望同步它們，以便它們包含相同的內容。

You must configure a remote that points to the upstream repository in Git to sync changes you make in a fork with the original repository. This also allows you to sync changes made in the original repository with the fork.
您必須組態一個指向 Git 中上游儲存庫的遠端儲存庫，以將您在 fork 中所做的更改與原始儲存庫同步。這還允許您將原始倉庫中所做的更改與複刻同步。

Step 1.  步驟 1.

Open a terminal and change the current working directory to your local project.
打開終端並將當前工作目錄更改為本地專案。

Step 2.  步驟 2。

List the current configured remote repository for your fork.
列出您的複刻當前組態的遠端倉庫。

$ git remote -v
 origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_FORK.git (fetch)
 origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_FORK.git (push)

Step 3.  步驟 3。

Specify a new remote upstream repository that will be synced with the fork.
指定將與複刻同步的新遠端上游倉庫。

$ git remote add upstream https://github.com/ORIGINAL_OWNER/ORIGINAL_REPOSITORY.git

Step 4.  步驟 4。

Verify the new upstream repository you’ve specified for your fork.
驗證您為複刻指定的新上游存儲庫。

$ git remote -v
 origin https://github.com/YOUR_USERNAME/YOUR_FORK.git (fetch)
